{"title_page": "(137108) 1999 AN10", "text_new": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:{{mp|(137108) 1999 AN|10}}}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox planet\n| minorplanet = yes\n| background = #FFC2E0\n| name = {{mp|(137108) 1999 AN|10}}\n| image = \n| caption = \n| discovery_ref = \n| discoverer = [[LINEAR]]\n| discovered = 13 January 1999\n| mpc_name = {{mp|(137108) 1999 AN|10}}\n| alt_names = \n| mp_category = {{Hlist\n | [[Near-Earth object|NEO]]\n | [[Apollo asteroid|Apollo]]\n | [[Potentially hazardous asteroid|PHA]]\n }}\n| orbit_ref = <ref name=\"jpldata\"/>\n| epoch = 13 January 2016 ([[Julian day|JD]]&nbsp;2457400.5)\n| aphelion = {{Convert|2.2787|AU|Gm|abbr=on|lk=on}}\n| perihelion = {{Convert|0.63875|AU|Gm|abbr=on}}\n| semimajor = {{Convert|1.4587|AU|Gm|abbr=on}}\n| eccentricity = 0.56212\n| period = 1.76&nbsp;[[Julian year (astronomy)|yr]] (643.51&nbsp;[[Julian year (astronomy)|d]])\n| inclination = 39.932\u00b0\n| asc_node = 314.41\u00b0\n| mean_anomaly = 186.69[[Degree (angle)|\u00b0]]\n| arg_peri = 268.30\u00b0\n| satellites = \n| dimensions = 800\u20131800&nbsp;m<ref name=\"phys\"/><ref name=h/>\n| mass = ~{{Val|2.9e12|ul=kg}}<ref name=\"estimate\"/>\n| escape_velocity = ~2.8&nbsp;km/h<ref name=\"estimate\"/>\n| abs_magnitude = 17.9<ref name=\"jpldata\"/>\n| mean_motion = {{Deg2DMS|0.55943|sup=ms}} / day (n)\n| observation_arc = 21222 days (58.10&nbsp;yr)\n| uncertainty = 0\n| moid = {{Convert|0.000708904|AU|km|abbr=on}}\n}}\n\n'''{{mp|(137108) 1999 AN|10}}''' is a kilometer-sized [[near-Earth asteroid]] and [[potentially hazardous asteroid]] of the [[Apollo asteroid|Apollo group]]. It was discovered by [[LINEAR]] on 13 January 1999.<ref name=Hannu/>\n\nOn 7 August 2027, this asteroid will pass within {{convert|0.0026|AU|km mi LD|abbr=on|lk=on}} of the Earth.<ref name=\"Sormano\"/><ref name=jpl-close/><ref name=\"neodys\"/><ref name=\"MPEC1999\"/> During the close approach, the asteroid should peak at about [[apparent magnitude]] 7.3,<ref name=\"NEODyS2027\"/> and will be visible in [[Binoculars#Astronomical|binoculars]].\n\n{{mp|1999 AN|10}} has a well determined orbit with an [[observation arc]] of 58 years.<ref name=\"jpldata\"/> It was found by Andreas Doppler and Arno Gn\u00e4dig in [[precovery]] images from 1955.<ref name=\"jpldata\"/> When {{mp|1999 AN|10}} only had an observation arc of 123 days, there was a 1 in 10 million chance that it could return on an impact trajectory in 2039.<ref name=\"JPL_Neop\"/>\n\nOn 7 August 1946, the asteroid passed {{convert|0.00625|AU|km mi|abbr=on|lk=on}} from Earth and then {{convert|0.00404|AU|km mi|abbr=on|lk=off}} from the Moon.<ref name=jpl-close/>\n[[File:Animation of 1999 AN10 orbit.gif|thumb|center|400px|Animation of 1999 AN10's orbit{{Snd}} Close approach in 2027<br />{{legend2| yellow| Sun}}{{\u00b7}}{{legend2| RoyalBlue| Earth}}{{\u00b7}}{{legend2| Magenta| 1999 AN10}}]]\n{{clear}}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Large near earth asteroid flybys 5LD}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs =\n\n<ref name=\"jpldata\">{{cite web |title =JPL Small-Body Database Browser: 137108 (1999 AN10) |url=https://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/sbdb.cgi?sstr=1999AN10 |accessdate=7 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"phys\">{{cite web\n |title        = 137108 1999 AN10\n |publisher    = The Near-Earth Asteroids Data Base at E.A.R.N\n |url          = http://earn.dlr.de/nea/137108.htm\n |accessdate   = 2008-01-31\n |archive-url  = https://www.webcitation.org/6B2zGwVjE?url=http://earn.dlr.de/nea/137108.htm\n |archive-date = 29 September 2012\n |url-status     = dead\n }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"h\">{{cite web\n  |title      = Asteroid Size Estimator\n  |publisher  = CNEOS NASA/JPL\n  |url        = https://cneos.jpl.nasa.gov/tools/ast_size_est.html\n  |accessdate = 20 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"estimate\">assume radius of 0.650&nbsp;km; [[Volume#Volume formulas|volume of a sphere]] * assume density of 2.6g/cm<sup>3</sup> (though it could be a loose [[rubble pile]]) yields a mass of {{Val|2.99e12|u=kg}} and an escape velocity of 2.82&nbsp;km/h.</ref>\n\n<ref name=Hannu>{{cite book\n  |last1 = Hannu\n  |first1 = Karttunen\n  |last2 = Vilppu\n  |first2 = Piirola\n  |title = Astrophysics with the NOT: Proceedings of the conference held in Turku on August 12\u201315, 1998\n  |publisher = University of Turku\n  |date = 1999\n  |pages = 270\n  |isbn = 951-29-1615-0}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Sormano\">{{cite web\n  |title=Sormano Astronomical Observatory: Table of Next Closest Approaches to the Earth by Asteroids \n  |publisher=Astronomical Observatory of Brera \n  |author1=Piero Sicoli \n  |author2=Francesco Manca \n  |url=http://www.brera.mi.astro.it/sormano/teca.html\n  |accessdate=2008-01-31 \n  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071201202009/http://www.brera.mi.astro.it/sormano/teca.html \n  |archivedate=1 December 2007 \n  |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"neodys\">{{cite web\n  |title       = NEODys (137108) 1999AN10\n  |publisher   = Department of Mathematics, University of Pisa, ITALY\n  |url         = http://newton.spacedys.com/neodys/index.php?pc=1.1.8&n=1999AN10\n  |accessdate  = 2008-01-31\n  |archiveurl  = https://www.webcitation.org/5g8QOV4pw?url=http://hamilton.dm.unipi.it/neodys/index.php?pc=1.1.8&n=1999AN10\n  |archivedate = 2009-04-18\n  |url-status     = live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MPEC1999\">{{cite web\n  |date=1999-07-12\n  |title=MPEC 1999-N21: 1999 AN10\n  |publisher=IAU: Minor Planet Center\n  |url=http://cfa-www.harvard.edu/mpec/J99/J99N21.html\n  |accessdate=2008-01-31}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=jpl-close>{{cite web\n  |type=2006-08-04 last obs (arc=51.5 years)\n  |title=JPL Close-Approach Data: 137108 (1999 AN10)\n  |url=https://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/sbdb.cgi?sstr=1999AN10;cad=1#cad\n  |accessdate=2011-10-17}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NEODyS2027\">{{cite web\n  |title=1999AN10 Ephemerides for 7 Aug 2027\n  |publisher=NEODyS (Near Earth Objects{{Snd}} Dynamic Site)\n  |url=http://newton.spacedys.com/neodys/index.php?pc=1.1.3.1&n=137108&oc=500&y0=2027&m0=08&d0=06&h0=0&mi0=0&y1=2027&m1=08&d1=08&h1=0&mi1=0&ti=1.0&tiu=hours\n  |accessdate=2011-10-16}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"JPL_Neop\">{{cite web\n  |title=The Continuing Story Of Asteroid 1999 AN10 \n  |author=Paul W. Chodas \n  |url=http://neo.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news017.html\n  |date=1999-05-18 \n  |accessdate=2010-10-22 \n  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101026082452/http://neo.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news017.html\n  |archivedate=26 October 2010 \n  |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n}} <!-- end of reflist -->\n\n== External links ==\n* {{AstDys|137108}}\n* {{JPL small body|id=137108}}\n\n{{Minor planets navigator| |number=137108 |PageName={{mp|(137108) 1999 AN|10}} | }}\n{{Small Solar System bodies}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:137108}}\n[[Category:Apollo asteroids]]\n[[Category:Discoveries by LINEAR]]\n[[Category:Potentially hazardous asteroids]]\n[[Category:Astronomical objects discovered in 1999|19990113]]\n", "text_old": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:{{mp|(137108) 1999 AN|10}}}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox planet\n| minorplanet = yes\n| background = #FFC2E0\n| name = {{mp|(137108) 1999 AN|10}}\n| image = \n| caption = \n| discovery_ref = \n| discoverer = [[LINEAR]]\n| discovered = 13 January 1999\n| mpc_name = {{mp|(137108) 1999 AN|10}}\n| alt_names = \n| mp_category = {{Hlist\n | [[Near-Earth object|NEO]]\n | [[Apollo asteroid|Apollo]]\n | [[Potentially hazardous asteroid|PHA]]\n }}\n| orbit_ref = <ref name=\"jpldata\"/>\n| epoch = 13 January 2016 ([[Julian day|JD]]&nbsp;2457400.5)\n| aphelion = {{Convert|2.2787|AU|Gm|abbr=on|lk=on}}\n| perihelion = {{Convert|0.63875|AU|Gm|abbr=on}}\n| semimajor = {{Convert|1.4587|AU|Gm|abbr=on}}\n| eccentricity = 0.56212\n| period = 1.76&nbsp;[[Julian year (astronomy)|yr]] (643.51&nbsp;[[Julian year (astronomy)|d]])\n| inclination = 39.932\u00b0\n| asc_node = 314.41\u00b0\n| mean_anomaly = 186.69[[Degree (angle)|\u00b0]]\n| arg_peri = 268.30\u00b0\n| satellites = \n| dimensions = 800\u20131800&nbsp;m<ref name=\"phys\"/><ref name=h/>\n| mass = ~